One DM asking me if I have any tips on organizing biographies for higher circulation and MY BRAIN GOES INTO OVERDRIVE!!

@hillbrew sent me the categories she was thinking of using in her space and we made them work for our collection!

Whipped up some new signage and added a call number suffix in our system so we could still search for books. Dewey is still here in the 92s… we just did a little facelift.

I am all about making YOUR library work best for YOUR kids. Organized, inviting, AND accessible.

✨🥰📚

Let’s do a builder gel mani! I was looking to get a sturdy gel base, but also have the ability to change my color without the trouble of gel removal. 

A builder gel base cures the clear gel (foundation, builder gel, top coat) before I put regular polish color and top coat on! I can remove the color and keep the gel base for my next mani. Keeps those nails sturdy and strong 🫶🏻

Every mani sesh always starts with toddler demands of nail stickers. To that we always say YAAAAS 🌈✨

Happy Sunday from this little babe one of my 5th graders whipped up 🤌🏼👩🏽‍💻🌱

I went back to the drawing board hardcore when it came to my 5th graders’ 3D printing projects this year. 

I know we all have collectively been dealing with lack of motivation at school one way or another. How do I even put into words the fact that 3D PRINTING was not even motivating for them? 

I am having so many of those moments where this “post pandemic teaching” life is changing up SO much of what my plans used to be to meet the needs of the students I have in front of me NOW. 

Kids used to LIVE for our 3D printing unit. Now, not so much. 

I always knew good teaching was adjusting your instruction to meet the needs of your kids, but we’ve all been in this crazy boat together the past couple of years where we are fighting the system and swimming upstream. 

I had a heart to heart with my students. I switched up my instruction. I tried a whole new approach. We all are feeling the spark again.🤞🏼👏🏼🫶🏻

Now if the 3D printers could just cooperate that’d be cool 😂🥹

Keep on keepin on team. 

(Last vid is our sweet collaborative 3D printed city from 6 or so years ago)

Incoming… deep post about ✨ShOuLdEr PaDs✨

Years ago I started working on body image in my therapy sessions. I remember specifically telling my therapist vivid details of when I started to notice my body as a child. How I STILL feel like my body “takes up too much space” today.

She then told me how her yoga instructor tells them at the end of every class to “take up space.” The same words, completely different viewpoint.

Idk the answer to any of this. I do know this blazer has shoulder pads and I am taking up space. Instead of trying to shrink myself I am sitting here thinking of all the things these shoulders carry and hold them high.

Swipe to see the non aesthetic real sit down pic of the mom tum 😂🫠 always keeping it real.

That concludes my deep post about ✨ShOuLdEr PaDs✨

Today I turn 34. 

It feels oddly monumental for me.

34 is a full lap.
34 is a full to do list.
34 is a full… stress level?
34 is a really full heart.

34 is having no clue what I am doing, but knowing I am exactly where I am meant to be.

34 is tired. Physically, mentally, emotionally, so freaking tired.

34 is trying to figure out who the heck I am and knowing exactly who I am all at the same time.

34 is squishy. All over. And tiny hands and feet always all over the squish. 

34 is lots of glimmers and lots of spirals. But knowing each is temporary.

34 is a continuing on the journey to balance. Of mom, teacher, business owner, wife, friend, and self. A forever journey with that one. 

34 is more listening, less talking. 

34. I love you already.

It is hair washing day y’all!

TBH - washing once or twice a week and investing in high quality hair tools over the years has saved this mane 🦁

After years and years of trying to perfect my mama/teacher waves here is where we are at. ALLL my holy grail products are listed in the steps below! 

This is the routine I have found manageable as a full time working mama and small biz owner 🤌🏼👏🏼

In a perfect world it would only 1.5 minutes to actually get the job done 🙃

Also peep that cameo from the 👵🏼 hairs peeking through - this is 34 BABY! 

1. mousse for lift - @colorwowhair 
2. rough dry - @dysonhair 
3. add a little tension while drying - @thewetbrush 
4. section off hair - clip from my etsy shop
5. curl small sections away from face - @t3micro 
6. separate curls with a wide tooth comb - @goodyhair 
7. spray away - @kenraprofessional 
8. straighten ends - @ghd_northamerica 
9. oil to lessen frizz and smooth! - @theouai

LET’S TALK ABOUT THE CALM KIT 🩵

3 years ago I had my first panic attack and entered the muddiest waters of my life as I became a first time mom at the height of the pandemic.

2 years ago I took all of my hard work with my doctors and therapist and turned it into the BRAVE BAGGIE as a resource for us all to keep close to us for grounding.

TODAY I send my next mental health project out into the world, The Calm Kit.

Being an elementary school teacher with a deep rooted passion for SEL and mom of two toddlers - the importance of emotional regulation, knowledge of big feelings, and grounding strategies are of high priority for me 24/7.

This year I moved from a giant school with a whole sensory room - to the cutest most lovely little building - but no spot for a calm corner in my packed library. 

I also pick up two very overstimulated children from daycare each day and the constant screaming is 😵‍💫

The Calm Kit is a portable little safe space with sensory tools to help my students and my children bring themselves back when the big feelings become too much and I am SO EXCITED to share it with you and yours 🫶🏻

(heck these would even make great teammate gifts or mom friend gifts as we head into this season of cray!)

LAUNCHING THIS THURSDAY - but I want to give away 5️⃣ Calm Kits to people this week before they hit the shelves 🫶🏻

Comment your favorite emoji you used when you’re stressed - and tag a friend who you want to send some calm to…

😒🙃😵‍💫😮‍💨😖😫 are my go-tos lollll

2023 was the year where I just kept putting one foot in front of the other. 

I just focused on doing the next right thing.

Packed up the library I poured my heart into the last 8 years to start in a new building.

Soaked up every minute of being a toddler mom.

And still managed to keep that small business of mine running. Because it makes my heart so happy to put art out into the world.

This year wasn’t full of big spectacular travels and giant life moments. But every single small one was as sweet as could be 🩵

AND HEY, I still managed to keep that passion for teaching in me alive 💜✨ how’s that for a win?! 🙃
